you, Mira, Athena.

01:08:00.350 --> 01:08:04.010
Mira, this morning would not
be complete without inviting

01:08:04.010 --> 01:08:08.690
you, as a young person in the
Bay Area, to speak for a moment

01:08:08.690 --> 01:08:10.940
about what does it
mean to encounter

01:08:10.940 --> 01:08:14.868
these stories, to work with your
art in reconnecting with them?

01:08:20.130 --> 01:08:21.460
MIRA: Hello, everyone.

01:08:21.460 --> 01:08:23.010
My name is Mira.

01:08:23.010 --> 01:08:26.450
I'm 16 years old, and I go to
a high school in Cupertino.

01:08:26.450 --> 01:08:28.170
I am one of the
performing members

01:08:28.170 --> 01:08:30.510
of Noorani Dance,
founded and directed

01:08:30.510 --> 01:08:34.020
by my [INAUDIBLE] teacher,
Farah Yasmeen Shaikh.

01:08:34.020 --> 01:08:36.390
I'm fortunate to be one
of the dancers featured

01:08:36.390 --> 01:08:38.040
in "The Parting."

01:08:38.040 --> 01:08:40.560
As the dance and music
director of "The Parting,"

01:08:40.560 --> 01:08:43.080
[INAUDIBLE] wanted to
include other styles

01:08:43.080 --> 01:08:47.130
of classical dance, such as
Bharatanatyam and Bengali

01:08:47.130 --> 01:08:49.710
and Punjabi folk dances.

01:08:49.710 --> 01:08:53.100
These multiple dance forms
represent the diversity

01:08:53.100 --> 01:08:57.060
of those that were affected
by the 1947 partition.

01:08:57.060 --> 01:08:59.700
With the actors, we will be
weaving different aspects

01:08:59.700 --> 01:09:02.010
of real-life events
of the partition

01:09:02.010 --> 01:09:05.220
through dance, music,
and a theatrical script.

01:09:05.220 --> 01:09:08.310
We hope to represent the
intensity and emotion

01:09:08.310 --> 01:09:13.500
of what took place during this
historic time in South Asia.

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:15.720
The partition has
always been puzzling.

01:09:15.720 --> 01:09:18.060
How could a man-made
line on a map

01:09:18.060 --> 01:09:21.660
displace over 14 million
people and result in the death

01:09:21.660 --> 01:09:23.430
of almost 2 million?

01:09:23.430 --> 01:09:25.319
South Asians of my
generation often

01:09:25.319 --> 01:09:28.120
don't understand the
magnitude of this tragedy.

01:09:28.120 --> 01:09:32.460
So taking part in this
project has special meaning

01:09:32.460 --> 01:09:33.990
to each of us.

01:09:33.990 --> 01:09:35.910
Through this experience,
we have become

01:09:35.910 --> 01:09:39.390
more empathetic to the
survivors of the partition.

01:09:39.390 --> 01:09:43.140
And we are also more
aware of the history

01:09:43.140 --> 01:09:45.510
of tension between
India and Pakistan

01:09:45.510 --> 01:09:48.450
and the forces of division
in the world today.

01:09:48.450 --> 01:09:50.609
We hope our generation
can learn from this

01:09:50.609 --> 01:09:54.390
and change the course of
history towards peace.

01:09:54.390 --> 01:09:57.496
Thank you, and I hope to see
you all at "The Parting."

